content: Hit and miss.  I have a rooted phone, so cannot use Android Pay.  So I got this app, and stored several of my cards on it.  When it works, it is great! For instance at Jamba Juice, I simply touched the reader that was it - nothing more to it.     In other instances, worse things happen.  At Trader Joe's, their POS froze hard when I touched my phone on their reader -- they had to close that register!  (My purchase was transferred to another register, where I used that same card in its physical manifestation).    At Starbucks, my purchase was declined -- and although it went through with that same physical card, I got a fraud alert from my bank (had to confirm that I did the purchase).
It always told me that invalid data.
